WEBVTT

00:01.459 --> 00:03.086
<i>Previously on</i> This Is Us...

00:03.169 --> 00:04.421
First day of summer.

00:04.504 --> 00:05.672
We don't want to be
the last ones in the pool.

00:06.715 --> 00:08.967
All right, gang, it's time
to get the hell out of here.

00:09.050 --> 00:10.051
How?

00:11.094 --> 00:12.262
We climb.

00:12.345 --> 00:14.848
You need to end it, Malik.

00:14.931 --> 00:16.266
You need to do it for her.

00:16.349 --> 00:18.476
What? I'm not gonna...

00:18.560 --> 00:20.228
-I love her.
-If you really love her, man,

00:20.311 --> 00:22.856
then you will do
what is best for her.

00:22.939 --> 00:24.941
He's acting so weird.

00:25.025 --> 00:26.901
He hasn't texted all morning.

00:28.528 --> 00:30.864
Senator Gamble's office
keeps calling.

00:30.947 --> 00:33.533
He saw the article
in <i>The Philadelphia Local</i>

00:33.616 --> 00:35.201
and sends his regards.

00:35.285 --> 00:37.120
Tell the senator I have to call
the old fart back

00:37.203 --> 00:38.371
after the holiday.

00:38.455 --> 00:41.124
REBECCA: In the event
that Miguel, God forbid,

00:41.207 --> 00:43.626
is not here to make
those decisions for me,

00:43.710 --> 00:45.628
I'm gonna need one of you
to stand in for him.

00:45.712 --> 00:48.048
Kate,

00:48.131 --> 00:49.257
I want it to be you.

00:49.341 --> 00:50.884
♪ ♪

00:56.765 --> 00:58.099
Come on, guys. Come on.

00:58.183 --> 00:59.434
First day of summer.

00:59.517 --> 01:01.061
We don't want to be
the last ones in the pool.

01:01.144 --> 01:03.271
-And you know what Mom and Dad
have for you guys.
-Oh!

01:03.355 --> 01:04.564
-Swim goggles!
-Swim goggles!

01:04.647 --> 01:06.900
-I want one!
-Chairs, chairs, chairs, chairs.

01:06.983 --> 01:08.818
REBECCA:
Hey, Bug, you want some goggles?

01:08.902 --> 01:10.570
KEVIN:
I want to go off
the diving board.

01:10.653 --> 01:11.946
JACK:
Don't you think you ought
to learn how to,

01:12.030 --> 01:13.782
-you know, swim first?
-REBECCA: Yeah, bud.

01:13.865 --> 01:15.742
I know you didn't like
taking your swim lessons,

01:15.825 --> 01:17.243
but they sure helped
your brother

01:17.327 --> 01:19.412
learn how to swim at the Y.

01:19.496 --> 01:21.539
KATE:
That girl is swimming
upside down.

01:21.623 --> 01:22.540
REBECCA:
No. (chuckles)

01:22.624 --> 01:24.376
She's doing the backstroke.

01:24.459 --> 01:26.795
And you would have learned how
to do that, too, if you stayed

01:26.878 --> 01:28.213
in class at the Y.

01:28.296 --> 01:30.882
There's Mr. Mike!
Can I go see him?

01:30.965 --> 01:33.259
Yeah. Yeah, of course.
Good luck.

01:33.343 --> 01:35.261
Actually, Randall, come here.

01:35.345 --> 01:36.554
Hey, hey, hey.

01:36.638 --> 01:39.891
So, um, I know
that your brother and sister

01:39.974 --> 01:42.227
didn't take to swimming
as fast as you did.

01:42.310 --> 01:45.397
And... I don't know,
I just had this whole idea of us

01:45.480 --> 01:47.148
swimming here together.

01:47.232 --> 01:49.150
But... maybe next summer.

01:49.234 --> 01:50.235
Yeah?

01:52.654 --> 01:54.572
Okay. Go get 'em, champ!

01:54.656 --> 01:55.990
-Go, go.
-JACK: Hey, you, uh...

01:56.074 --> 01:58.284
-you got Kate?
-REBECCA: Yeah. I got Kate.

01:58.368 --> 01:59.661
RANDALL:
I'm here, I'm here!

01:59.744 --> 02:01.413
-Don't start without me!
-(chuckles) I wouldn't dream

02:01.496 --> 02:02.872
of starting
without my star student.

02:02.956 --> 02:04.082
Up top!

02:04.165 --> 02:05.083
(both imitating bubbling)

02:05.166 --> 02:06.167
(chuckles)

02:07.210 --> 02:09.045
All right, troops. Now,

02:09.129 --> 02:12.340
you five have rocked it
all summer at the Y.

02:12.424 --> 02:13.341
Today's the day.

02:13.425 --> 02:14.676
So, how it's gonna go--

02:14.759 --> 02:15.969
first, we're gonna start

02:16.052 --> 02:18.138
with a timed
underwater breathing exercise.

02:18.221 --> 02:20.807
Then you're gonna swim
the whole length of the pool.

02:20.890 --> 02:24.227
Then, after that, you're gonna
tread water for about a minute.

02:24.310 --> 02:27.856
And then we'll finish
floating on our backs and done.

02:28.857 --> 02:30.859
-KATE: Uh-uh. No.
-KEVIN: Okay, hey, look, relax.

02:30.942 --> 02:32.402
-We're gonna try it again.
-No! I can't.

02:32.485 --> 02:34.279
I can't. No.

02:35.655 --> 02:37.657
-(siren whoops)
-(vehicle approaching)

02:37.741 --> 02:39.576
-(brakes squeak)
-(indistinct radio transmission)

02:40.827 --> 02:42.245
(quietly):
Damn it.

02:42.328 --> 02:44.414
We're getting arrested.

02:45.957 --> 02:47.625
Great.

02:48.668 --> 02:51.087
Oh, thank you so much, sir.

02:52.505 --> 02:53.631
Is that beer?

02:53.715 --> 02:55.300
No.

02:55.383 --> 02:56.760
(clanging)

02:56.843 --> 02:58.470
Pick that up.

02:58.553 --> 03:00.055
Yes, sir.

03:04.434 --> 03:06.353
Give me that.

03:06.436 --> 03:07.896
It-it is beer.

03:10.482 --> 03:13.693
All right. So that's illegal
trespassing, underage drinking.

03:13.777 --> 03:17.030
I'd say that you guys are in
for a very unpleasant night.

03:18.073 --> 03:19.949
Wait right here.

03:22.535 --> 03:24.829
This can't be happening.

03:26.873 --> 03:28.792
-Just wait right here.
I'll-I'll be right back.
-Randall.

03:28.875 --> 03:30.877
-KEVIN: Hey, hey, hey.
Don't make it worse.
-Randall.

03:30.960 --> 03:32.837
I can handle this.

03:33.922 --> 03:34.964
Excuse me, sir?

03:35.048 --> 03:36.257
Whoa.

03:36.341 --> 03:37.467
Just 30 seconds.

03:38.468 --> 03:39.594
<i>REBECCA:</i>
<i>I need you all</i>

03:39.678 --> 03:41.012
to hear my voice right now.

03:41.096 --> 03:42.263
Your mother's voice,

03:42.347 --> 03:44.265
with all of her faculties.

03:44.349 --> 03:45.600
(inhales)

03:46.643 --> 03:49.771
<i>You will not make your lives</i>
<i>smaller because of me.</i>

03:49.854 --> 03:53.274
<i>This thing</i>
<i>that's happening to me</i>

03:53.358 --> 03:56.403
will not be the thing
that holds you back.

03:56.486 --> 03:59.114
So, take the risks.

03:59.197 --> 04:01.116
Make the big moves,

04:01.199 --> 04:03.451
even if they're small moves.

04:03.535 --> 04:06.121
Forge ahead with your lives

04:06.204 --> 04:09.374
in any and every direction
that moves you.

04:09.457 --> 04:12.293
I am your mother,

04:12.377 --> 04:15.046
and I'm sick.

04:15.130 --> 04:18.174
And I'm asking you
to be fearless.

04:30.520 --> 04:31.938
(grunts)

04:33.148 --> 04:35.275
(inhales deeply, exhales)

04:35.358 --> 04:37.444
I'm sure
she has her reasons, hon.

04:37.527 --> 04:40.030
No, I know.

04:40.113 --> 04:41.531
And it's Thanksgiving.

04:41.614 --> 04:42.615
Mm?

04:42.699 --> 04:44.034
We knew
there was gonna be drama.

04:44.117 --> 04:46.119
(clicks tongue)
Yeah...

04:47.162 --> 04:48.163
No, it's okay. I get it.

04:48.246 --> 04:50.582
It's just, uh...

04:50.665 --> 04:52.042
It's a lot to process.

04:52.125 --> 04:53.793
-Mm.
-(rapid footsteps approaching)

04:55.295 --> 04:58.965
Wow, I just figured out why
Malik has been being so weird.

04:59.049 --> 05:01.968
You told him
to stay away from me?

05:02.052 --> 05:04.512
-Dej...
-He broke up with me.

05:07.307 --> 05:09.392
I literally hate you.

05:09.476 --> 05:11.269
Hey. Deja.

05:11.353 --> 05:13.063
-You don't mean that.
-No, no, I do.

05:13.146 --> 05:14.564
I do. He lied to me.
You lied to me.

05:14.647 --> 05:16.483
How did I lie to you?

05:16.566 --> 05:17.984
You walked around for weeks,

05:18.068 --> 05:19.402
staring in my face,

05:19.486 --> 05:20.737
acting like nothing happened,

05:20.820 --> 05:22.030
when you know what you did.

05:23.323 --> 05:25.950
I didn't think
he would listen to me. Okay?

05:26.034 --> 05:27.994
You kids are notorious
for not listening.

05:28.078 --> 05:30.330
Hey, hey. Why don't we all
just calm down, all right?

05:30.413 --> 05:32.707
It is late.
Emotions are at a ten right now,

05:32.791 --> 05:34.876
and this is a very old house
with very thin walls.

05:34.959 --> 05:36.586
Is everything okay?

05:36.670 --> 05:37.587
We heard yelling.

05:37.671 --> 05:38.755
Case in point.

05:38.838 --> 05:40.006
Um...

05:40.090 --> 05:41.591
just a little family issue.

05:41.675 --> 05:43.802
RANDALL:
Deja, dropping out

05:43.885 --> 05:46.304
of high school to get your GED
and move to Boston

05:46.388 --> 05:48.723
to live with your 18-year-old
single father boyfriend,

05:48.807 --> 05:51.476
that is not good enough for you.

05:51.559 --> 05:53.687
-You deserve better.
-You don't get to decide that.

05:53.770 --> 05:55.355
Well, yeah, I do.
You're my daughter!

05:55.438 --> 05:56.523
No, I'm not!

05:57.857 --> 06:00.360
Tess and Annie
are your daughters.

06:00.443 --> 06:03.071
I'm just some girl
you took from her mom.

06:11.955 --> 06:13.957
♪ ♪

06:26.886 --> 06:29.472
(birds chirping)

06:30.932 --> 06:33.309
-Hey.
-Hey.

06:33.393 --> 06:34.519
Heard you had
a rough night in there.

06:34.602 --> 06:35.770
You all right?

06:35.854 --> 06:38.690
Uh, all part of being the parent
of a teenager.

06:38.773 --> 06:41.526
-Mm.
-As you'll see all too soon.

06:41.609 --> 06:43.528
Yo. Safe travels, siblings!

06:43.611 --> 06:45.488
'Kay. We'll see you guys in L.A.

06:45.572 --> 06:46.948
for Mom and Mig's
anniversary party.

06:47.032 --> 06:47.949
-KEVIN: All right.
-Love you.

06:48.033 --> 06:49.034
RANDALL:
Love you.

06:50.076 --> 06:53.913
Well, I am off to start
my fearless best life for Mom.

06:53.997 --> 06:55.498
-Mm.
-Whatever that means.

06:55.582 --> 06:57.584
-Do you, brother.
-(chuckles)

06:57.667 --> 06:58.960
-Be good.
-You, too.

06:59.044 --> 07:00.628
-All right.
-All right.

07:05.800 --> 07:07.135
REBECCA:
Hmm.

07:07.218 --> 07:08.345
Hey.

07:08.428 --> 07:09.763
You guys sticking around
for breakfast?

07:09.846 --> 07:10.972
We're having leftovers.

07:11.056 --> 07:12.140
And pie.

07:12.223 --> 07:13.850
Um... no.

07:13.933 --> 07:15.769
But thanks.

07:15.852 --> 07:16.853
BETH:
God.

07:17.896 --> 07:18.980
I can't find her anywhere.

07:19.064 --> 07:21.399
-Who?
-Deja. She's not in the house.

07:23.276 --> 07:25.278
(exhales)

07:31.951 --> 07:33.536
-Where is she?
-I don't know.

07:33.620 --> 07:35.914
-I woke up
and she was already gone.
-Tess?

07:36.998 --> 07:37.916
Tess?

07:37.999 --> 07:39.042
I don't want you to get mad.

07:39.125 --> 07:40.377
I'm already there.

07:40.460 --> 07:41.836
Where's your sister?

07:43.046 --> 07:44.297
She left last night.

07:44.381 --> 07:46.174
She what?

07:46.257 --> 07:48.051
She was really upset. And
I tried to talk her out of it,

07:48.134 --> 07:50.804
but she wouldn't listen to me.
So she took off.

07:50.887 --> 07:53.807
She went to talk Malik
into getting back together.

07:53.890 --> 07:56.393
-Oh, good Lord.
-I can't believe
she would do this.

07:58.311 --> 08:01.064
-Where you going?
-To get my daughter.

08:01.147 --> 08:02.273
<i>(door opens)</i>

08:02.357 --> 08:04.275
Should I go with you?

08:04.359 --> 08:05.944
I mean,
we'd have to take the girls.

08:06.027 --> 08:08.530
Hey, guys. I know this is a lot,

08:08.613 --> 08:10.156
but let's take a deep breath

08:10.240 --> 08:12.242
and it will feel
less overwhelming.

08:12.325 --> 08:13.618
Or maybe we should just let Kate
handle it,

08:13.702 --> 08:15.537
since she handles
all the big stuff now.

08:19.791 --> 08:21.626
Hey, Miguel,
I hate to put you out, man,

08:21.710 --> 08:23.712
but could you give Beth and
the girls a ride back to Philly?

08:23.795 --> 08:25.505
Uh, sure. Yeah, I can do that.

08:25.588 --> 08:27.465
Thank you.
I'll call you from the road.

08:27.549 --> 08:28.800
All right.
I'll keep trying Deja.

08:28.883 --> 08:30.093
Yeah.

08:34.180 --> 08:36.057
-Mom, what are you doing?
-I'm coming with you.

08:36.141 --> 08:38.977
Hey, Miguel. Could you grab
my bags for me, please?

08:41.021 --> 08:42.063
That's really not necessary.

08:42.147 --> 08:43.732
I am coming with you.

08:44.899 --> 08:46.651
Get in the car.

08:51.156 --> 08:53.491
<i>(footsteps)</i>

08:53.575 --> 08:55.285
<i>(car door opens)</i>

08:56.745 --> 08:57.746
<i>(car door shuts)</i>

09:01.374 --> 09:02.542
<i>(line ringing)</i>

09:02.625 --> 09:03.710
Come on.

09:03.793 --> 09:05.211
(Randall clicks tongue)

09:05.295 --> 09:07.047
-Hmm...
<i>-Your call has been forwarded</i>

09:07.130 --> 09:09.215
<i>to an automatic voice...</i>

09:09.299 --> 09:12.302
Malik's not picking up, either.

09:12.385 --> 09:14.346
I swear, when I get to Boston,
I'm gonna...

09:14.429 --> 09:15.889
-(exhales)
-What?

09:15.972 --> 09:18.224
Do you even know what you're
gonna do when you get there?

09:18.308 --> 09:20.060
I haven't got it
all mapped out, Mom,

09:20.143 --> 09:21.728
but throwing Deja
over my shoulder

09:21.811 --> 09:24.230
and zip-tying her to
the backseat has come to mind.

09:25.273 --> 09:26.649
Phone.

09:27.650 --> 09:29.903
You know the car
has Bluetooth, right?

09:29.986 --> 09:32.280
If Malik were to have picked up
the phone,

09:32.364 --> 09:33.490
do you think
what you would say to him

09:33.573 --> 09:34.824
would help or hurt
the situation?

09:34.908 --> 09:36.659
(exhales)

09:37.702 --> 09:39.371
Phone.

09:40.288 --> 09:42.082
Thank you.

09:45.293 --> 09:46.920
(sighs)

09:49.923 --> 09:51.132
(Randall exhales)

10:02.936 --> 10:05.021
She's done this before.

10:06.981 --> 10:09.317
A few months ago.

10:09.401 --> 10:11.194
She told me and Beth
she was going to a sleepover,

10:11.277 --> 10:12.987
and she hopped on a bus
to Boston.

10:14.114 --> 10:15.490
Mm.

10:18.410 --> 10:21.079
I was not like this with Beth.

10:21.162 --> 10:22.706
No, you were not.

10:22.789 --> 10:23.998
But...

10:25.000 --> 10:28.795
...not everyone's
first love story is the same.

10:31.589 --> 10:33.925
Mine was with Chris Bellose.

10:35.135 --> 10:36.386
I was 15.

10:36.469 --> 10:38.638
He was... much too old for me.

10:38.722 --> 10:39.806
(chuckles softly)

10:40.849 --> 10:42.350
(sighs)
I was head over heels for him.

10:42.434 --> 10:45.103
He looked like James Dean.

10:45.186 --> 10:46.813
Had the cutest butt.

10:46.896 --> 10:47.981
-No.
-Yeah.

10:48.064 --> 10:49.607
-No. Stop.
-The cutest, little,

10:49.691 --> 10:50.650
-tight... Yeah.
-Okay.

10:50.734 --> 10:52.152
(chuckles)

10:54.154 --> 10:56.281
I can't imagine you at 15.

10:56.364 --> 10:57.699
REBECCA:
Mm.

11:03.371 --> 11:06.291
This morning, when you mentioned
Kate handling the big things...

11:06.374 --> 11:08.501
That was a stupid joke.
That's all.

11:08.585 --> 11:09.586
Shouldn't have said it.

11:11.629 --> 11:13.381
Okay.

11:16.718 --> 11:19.304
You think we might be able to
stop for something to eat soon?

11:19.387 --> 11:22.515
I can't, um, take my meds
on an empty stomach.

11:22.599 --> 11:24.267
Uh, yeah. Say no more.

11:27.729 --> 11:29.898
WAITRESS:
Iced tea
and two pastrami sandwiches

11:29.981 --> 11:31.399
-on rye.
-Mmm.
-Thanks.

11:31.483 --> 11:34.194
Thank you, Samantha.

11:34.277 --> 11:36.821
Um, actually...

11:36.905 --> 11:38.740
do you mind taking a picture

11:38.823 --> 11:40.575
-for us?
-Mom, really?

11:40.658 --> 11:43.328
-What? Just one.
-Mom, she's busy.

11:43.411 --> 11:45.622
-I-I look like crap. Come on.
What are we doing here?
-Oh, I'm sorry.

11:45.705 --> 11:48.166
Yesterday, you were obsessed
with taking photos of me.

11:48.249 --> 11:50.835
And now, today,
you're some shy teenager?

11:50.919 --> 11:52.796
-Okay.
-You guys celebrating something?

11:52.879 --> 11:56.591
No. Just, uh, a day with my son.

11:56.675 --> 11:57.676
Mm.

11:59.803 --> 12:00.762
You like 'em?

12:00.845 --> 12:01.763
I can take more.

12:01.846 --> 12:02.931
-Oh.
-(sucks teeth)

12:03.014 --> 12:04.391
No, these are perfect.

12:04.474 --> 12:05.684
-Could you, uh...?
-I'll AirDrop you.

12:05.767 --> 12:06.851
-Beautiful.
-Yeah.

12:06.935 --> 12:09.145
-She'll AirDrop me.
-Mm-hmm.

12:09.229 --> 12:10.939
(grunts)

12:11.022 --> 12:12.190
Looks good.

12:12.273 --> 12:13.566
Enjoy.

12:13.650 --> 12:16.152
♪ <i>We met up</i>
<i>with some heavy people</i> ♪

12:16.236 --> 12:17.237
Mmm, mmm, mmm.

12:17.320 --> 12:18.321
It's good?

12:18.405 --> 12:19.447
-Mm-hmm.
-Good.

12:19.531 --> 12:20.990
Mm.

12:21.074 --> 12:24.828
-♪ <i>Up in southern Illinois</i> ♪
-(pills rattling)

12:27.330 --> 12:31.209
♪ <i>They took us way out</i>
<i>in the country</i> ♪

12:34.045 --> 12:38.508
♪ <i>And gave us all</i>
<i>a place to stay</i> ♪

12:38.591 --> 12:41.177
♪ <i>Hey, hey...</i> ♪

12:41.261 --> 12:42.846
(sighs)

12:42.929 --> 12:45.807
-Sorry, they make these things
so hard to open.
-Mm-hmm.

12:48.393 --> 12:49.769
(clears throat) How many?

12:49.853 --> 12:51.271
Two.

12:51.354 --> 12:52.647
-Thanks.
-Yeah.

12:54.482 --> 12:57.944
-This is my life now. (chuckles)
-♪ <i>They had farmhouse</i>
<i>and a trailer</i> ♪

13:00.822 --> 13:03.908
-♪ <i>They had some sails</i>
<i>and a lot of land</i> ♪
-(Rebecca exhales)

13:07.328 --> 13:09.456
♪ <i>They said they farm</i>
<i>all through...</i> ♪

13:09.539 --> 13:13.084
It was, um... Eat'n Park.

13:14.502 --> 13:16.212
The first time
I saw you do that.

13:16.296 --> 13:19.924
You were six or seven.

13:21.134 --> 13:22.510
And we spent that summer

13:22.594 --> 13:25.847
working on your Scholastic
Book Club reading list.

13:25.930 --> 13:27.849
-Wow. That is a throwback.
-Mm.

13:27.932 --> 13:30.352
I was obsessed with that thing.

13:30.435 --> 13:31.978
Yes, you were obsessed.

13:32.062 --> 13:34.397
You wanted to beat
everyone in your class

13:34.481 --> 13:37.859
-and read all the books
on the list.
-Yeah.

13:37.942 --> 13:39.819
And we would sit in the living
room reading together

13:39.903 --> 13:41.237
each night on the couch,

13:41.321 --> 13:43.782
<i>while Kevin and Kate</i>
<i>and Dad watched TV.</i>

13:43.865 --> 13:45.533
<i>Do you remember that?</i>

13:46.576 --> 13:48.161
-I do.
-Yeah.

13:48.244 --> 13:50.038
And every Friday in the summer,

13:50.121 --> 13:52.290
we would get to the library
before it opened,

13:52.374 --> 13:56.252
and we would
stay until it closed.

13:57.253 --> 14:00.256
And then I would take you
to Eat'n Park-- just us.

14:00.340 --> 14:01.800
We'd always get
the smiley face cookie.

14:01.883 --> 14:03.968
Yes. Yes.

14:04.052 --> 14:05.470
That was our favorite part,
remember?

14:05.553 --> 14:06.971
It was. Yeah.

14:07.055 --> 14:08.723
Mm.

14:10.642 --> 14:13.395
(phone ringing)

14:14.437 --> 14:15.897
That's my phone.

14:15.980 --> 14:17.440
Oh, right.

14:17.524 --> 14:18.775
Yeah.

14:18.858 --> 14:20.318
Sorry.

14:20.402 --> 14:22.320
It's Beth.

14:24.531 --> 14:25.657
Babe?

14:25.740 --> 14:27.367
<i>BETH:</i>
<i>So I finally got ahold of Deja.</i>

14:27.450 --> 14:28.368
Where is she?

14:28.451 --> 14:29.536
<i>She got to Boston.</i>

14:29.619 --> 14:31.079
<i>She's with Malik.</i>

14:31.162 --> 14:33.415
<i>She wanted us to know she's fine</i>
<i>and to stop worrying.</i>

14:33.498 --> 14:34.916
Uh, we're in Connecticut.

14:35.000 --> 14:36.960
-We could be there
in a few hours.
<i>-Okay.</i>

14:37.043 --> 14:38.753
<i>-I love you.</i>
-Love you, too.

14:38.837 --> 14:40.505
Uh, we should hit the road.

14:40.588 --> 14:42.340
-Probably be there
before nightfall.
-Yeah.

14:42.424 --> 14:44.342
Can I give you a little advice?

14:44.426 --> 14:45.719
Mm-hmm.

14:46.845 --> 14:48.513
Give her some space.

14:48.596 --> 14:51.307
♪ <i>We were sitting</i>
<i>'round the trailer...</i> ♪

14:51.391 --> 14:53.184
-Space?
-Yeah.

14:53.268 --> 14:56.604
Yeah, give her a little bit
of space to figure this out.

14:56.688 --> 14:58.106
Just for a night.

14:58.189 --> 15:00.817
You know, she said
we shouldn't worry about her,

15:00.900 --> 15:03.695
so try to trust that.

15:07.407 --> 15:11.327
-♪ <i>And putting away</i>
<i>that highland blues</i> ♪
-(clicks tongue)

15:11.411 --> 15:13.538
♪ <i>And the reefer, too...</i> ♪

15:14.831 --> 15:18.793
So if we're not hitting
the road, what do we do now?

15:20.962 --> 15:22.172
(clicks tongue)

15:22.255 --> 15:25.675
Well, I-I did see a bar
down the block.

15:25.759 --> 15:28.345
You fancy a drink with old Mom?

15:28.428 --> 15:30.180
♪ <i>Him and his lady,</i>
<i>they dug the country...</i> ♪

15:34.642 --> 15:36.644
♪ ♪

15:42.317 --> 15:43.234
(stopwatch beeps)

15:43.318 --> 15:45.153
Thirty-five seconds.

15:45.236 --> 15:47.197
That's got to be
a new swim test record.

15:47.280 --> 15:49.199
-I can go for longer.
-Oh, no, no, no, no.

15:49.282 --> 15:52.452
I believe you, but I also want
to keep my teaching license.

15:52.535 --> 15:53.745
Uh, let's go see what
your swim mates are up to

15:53.828 --> 15:54.871
and get them ready for part two.

15:54.954 --> 15:56.498
REBECCA:
Come on.
He's just a child, Jack.

15:56.581 --> 15:58.333
-Yeah, someday,
he's gonna be a man.
-(Kevin coughing)

15:58.416 --> 16:00.418
REBECCA:
I'm trying to get her
to put her face in the water,

16:00.502 --> 16:03.672
-so good luck with that.
-JACK: Okay. Here.

16:03.755 --> 16:05.882
Hey, Randall, come on. Let's go.

16:08.551 --> 16:10.887
♪ ♪

16:20.522 --> 16:22.148
OFFICER:
All right.

16:22.232 --> 16:23.733
You're free to go.

16:25.694 --> 16:27.654
Next time, don't litter.

16:30.907 --> 16:32.742
Happy Thanksgiving.

16:36.913 --> 16:38.373
(laughs, gasps)

16:38.456 --> 16:39.582
How did you pull that off?

16:39.666 --> 16:40.875
We just talked.

16:40.959 --> 16:42.210
He was a reasonable guy.

16:42.293 --> 16:44.462
You're telling me
what you said, okay?

16:44.546 --> 16:46.464
-You're telling me
what you said.
-Yeah, whatever.

16:46.548 --> 16:47.632
It's getting late.
We should head home.

16:47.716 --> 16:49.718
Right, or...

16:49.801 --> 16:51.136
There's another option
on the table.

16:51.219 --> 16:52.929
We could head to the diner.
I have the keys.

16:54.222 --> 16:55.849
I don't want to go home yet.

16:55.932 --> 16:57.267
It's depressing.

16:57.350 --> 16:59.269
And think about it,
when was the last time

16:59.352 --> 17:01.021
the three of us
were all together like this?

17:03.064 --> 17:04.524
I'm game.

17:04.607 --> 17:05.775
KATE:
Yes.

17:05.859 --> 17:07.777
Randall?

17:10.905 --> 17:12.323
Voilà.

17:12.407 --> 17:14.367
Are you sure
we're allowed in here?

17:14.451 --> 17:16.244
We've broken enough laws
for one night.

17:16.327 --> 17:18.079
Jukebox. Sweet.

17:18.163 --> 17:20.749
Randall, my manager's out sick,
like, five days a week.

17:20.832 --> 17:22.459
I practically run the place.
We're fine.

17:22.542 --> 17:24.502
Okay.

17:24.586 --> 17:26.254
(coins clanging)

17:27.714 --> 17:30.175
Hey, uh, do you guys
have a phone?

17:30.258 --> 17:31.676
I want to call Mom,
let her know where we are.

17:31.760 --> 17:33.345
Yeah, phone's in the office.

17:33.428 --> 17:34.888
-Thanks.
-Mm-hmm.

17:34.971 --> 17:37.098
<i>(upbeat music playing)</i>

17:37.182 --> 17:38.641
(lively chatter)

17:38.725 --> 17:39.893
Mm.

17:39.976 --> 17:42.395
(laughs)

17:42.479 --> 17:43.980
What's so funny?

17:44.064 --> 17:45.940
-The floor is sticky.
-Ah.

17:46.024 --> 17:48.568
I haven't been
to a-a bar in years,

17:48.651 --> 17:50.695
but the floor, always sticky.

17:50.779 --> 17:53.740
I don't even want to know what
substances contributed to that.

17:53.823 --> 17:56.826
Should we, should we get
a selfie? Come on.

17:56.910 --> 17:58.620
Is this gonna be
an all-day thing?

17:58.703 --> 18:00.038
-Oh, yeah. Yeah.
-Okay.

18:00.121 --> 18:01.790
Here we go.

18:01.873 --> 18:03.958
-Mm. That was...
-Beautiful.

18:04.042 --> 18:05.502
Oh, after you.

18:06.878 --> 18:08.713
-Oh.
-Mm-hmm.

18:08.797 --> 18:10.465
-(clears throat)
-Ah.

18:10.548 --> 18:12.509
-(exhales)
-Ooh.

18:12.592 --> 18:14.177
What can I get you?

18:14.260 --> 18:17.263
Hi. Uh, we would like
two glasses

18:17.347 --> 18:19.432
of your Chianti Classico,
please.

18:22.852 --> 18:25.230
I got red and white,
both room temp.

18:25.313 --> 18:26.398
Excellent.

18:26.481 --> 18:28.566
Uh, we'll take your red, please.

18:28.650 --> 18:29.901
-BARTENDER: You bet.
-All right.

18:29.984 --> 18:31.736
-Sure.
-(laughs)

18:32.737 --> 18:35.073
Since when do you drink
Chianti Classico?

18:35.156 --> 18:36.908
(chuckles)

18:37.909 --> 18:39.452
(clears throat)

18:43.331 --> 18:44.666
REBECCA:
"Five Fun Facts

18:44.749 --> 18:47.377
"about Controversial Councilman
Pearson.

18:47.460 --> 18:50.422
Number one: I love
a nice glass of Chianti."

18:50.505 --> 18:51.631
(Rebecca chuckles)

18:51.715 --> 18:53.425
I can't believe you have this.

18:53.508 --> 18:54.801
Are you kidding me?

18:54.884 --> 18:57.095
I collect anything
and everything about you kids.

18:57.178 --> 18:58.471
Ah, look at this.

18:58.555 --> 19:00.974
"What is Councilman Pearson
reading right now?"

19:01.057 --> 19:02.809
-Uh-huh.
-(humming)

19:04.978 --> 19:06.730
<i>Homegoing.</i>

19:06.813 --> 19:08.815
In the article, you mention
that you cried like a baby

19:08.898 --> 19:11.526
when Marjorie brought
Marcus to the Cape Castle.

19:11.609 --> 19:12.944
(sighs) I did, too.

19:13.028 --> 19:15.488
Just sobbed.

19:15.572 --> 19:16.656
-RANDALL: Ah.
-REBECCA: Oh.

19:16.740 --> 19:17.991
<i>Buon appetito.</i>

19:18.074 --> 19:19.325
-RANDALL: <i>Grazie.</i>
-REBECCA: Thank you.

19:20.368 --> 19:22.579
Ah. Want to get your phone?

19:22.662 --> 19:24.039
Get a little wine selfie?

19:25.081 --> 19:26.583
-Sure.
-All right.

19:26.666 --> 19:29.169
-(clears throat)
-That's the spirit.

19:29.252 --> 19:31.212
-(sucks teeth) And...
-Oh.

19:31.296 --> 19:32.922
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

19:33.006 --> 19:34.007
(camera snaps)

19:34.090 --> 19:35.508
Wow, that's a good one.

19:35.592 --> 19:37.260
RANDALL:
That's a good one.

19:37.344 --> 19:38.511
REBECCA:
Mm.

19:38.595 --> 19:40.805
-Hmm?
-They have a dartboard.

19:40.889 --> 19:43.558
Your father and I used to play
darts all the time at Froggy's.

19:43.641 --> 19:45.018
RANDALL:
Hmm.

19:45.101 --> 19:47.145
You want to play?

19:48.855 --> 19:50.815
Yeah, sure. Well, why not?

19:50.899 --> 19:51.858
(exhales)

19:51.941 --> 19:53.360
Know what?

19:53.443 --> 19:55.236
We don't need pictures of it.

19:56.488 --> 19:58.073
I'll remember this part.

19:58.156 --> 20:00.367
And you will, too.

20:00.450 --> 20:01.910
I promise.

20:03.912 --> 20:04.913
Come on.

20:04.996 --> 20:06.331
Let me go kick your butt.

20:06.414 --> 20:08.249
-Oh, really?
-Yeah, let me show you

20:08.333 --> 20:10.085
-how it's done.
-It's like that.

20:12.921 --> 20:15.965
♪ ♪

20:20.470 --> 20:22.055
(phone dialing)

20:22.138 --> 20:23.098
Uh...

20:23.181 --> 20:24.891
<i>(line ringing)</i>

20:24.974 --> 20:26.017
<i>REBECCA:</i>
<i>Hello?</i>

20:26.101 --> 20:27.227
Hey.

20:27.310 --> 20:29.979
<i>Randall. It's almost 11:00.</i>

20:30.063 --> 20:32.399
And I have a pulse,
and I found a phone.

20:32.482 --> 20:35.318
<i>We're just at Kate's diner,</i>
<i>goofing off.</i>

20:35.402 --> 20:37.779
It's actually nice. Been a while
since we all hung out.

20:39.072 --> 20:40.240
Yeah.

20:42.158 --> 20:43.076
You doing okay?

20:43.159 --> 20:44.953
(inhales)

20:45.036 --> 20:47.539
I will be.
(exhales)

20:50.750 --> 20:53.294
Uh, Kate told me about Miguel.

20:55.171 --> 20:58.216
I don't know why
I'm taking this so hard.

20:58.299 --> 21:00.218
<i>He was a big part of your life.</i>

21:01.511 --> 21:04.264
You know, it's natural
to feel, uh...

21:05.640 --> 21:07.726
...yeah, no, just to feel.

21:07.809 --> 21:09.185
<i>Yeah, well, I am...</i>

21:09.269 --> 21:10.770
I'm feeling.

21:10.854 --> 21:12.313
(inhales)

21:12.397 --> 21:15.108
Anyway, you know what?
Don't let me keep you.

21:15.191 --> 21:16.651
You go enjoy your evening

21:16.735 --> 21:18.194
with your brother and sister,
all right?

21:18.278 --> 21:20.071
Hey, uh...

21:20.155 --> 21:22.282
could you check
the right pocket of my backpack?

21:22.365 --> 21:23.742
I think it's on the couch.

21:26.828 --> 21:27.912
Yeah, it's right here.

21:27.996 --> 21:28.913
<i>Open it.</i>

21:28.997 --> 21:30.415
(sniffles)

21:31.416 --> 21:32.792
(sighs)

21:35.045 --> 21:37.005
♪ ♪

21:40.925 --> 21:42.761
Our cookies.

21:42.844 --> 21:44.387
<i>(chuckles) Yeah.</i>
<i>I stopped by Eat'n Park</i>

21:44.471 --> 21:45.597
on my way home.

21:45.680 --> 21:46.890
I wanted to give it to you
before dinner,

21:46.973 --> 21:49.517
but a lot was going on.

21:49.601 --> 21:50.977
<i>Randall, thank you.</i>

21:51.061 --> 21:51.978
<i>This is...</i>

21:52.062 --> 21:53.563
I-I needed this.

21:53.646 --> 21:54.731
(exhales)

21:54.814 --> 21:56.066
<i>You're welcome.</i>

21:57.817 --> 21:59.694
Mom, now, don't eat it all.
Come on.

21:59.778 --> 22:01.029
What are you talking about?

22:01.112 --> 22:03.073
-You got these cookies for me.
<i>-No, Mom.</i>

22:03.156 --> 22:05.200
Sharing is caring.
You taught me that. (chuckles)

22:12.415 --> 22:13.792
Well...

22:13.875 --> 22:16.836
at least their only room left
is also their finest.

22:16.920 --> 22:18.296
(Rebecca chuckles)

22:18.380 --> 22:20.465
You sure you're okay with this?

22:21.508 --> 22:22.592
It's lovely.

22:24.594 --> 22:26.096
Okey dokey.

22:34.813 --> 22:35.980
(spits)

22:51.746 --> 22:55.125
You have more gray
in your beard.

22:55.208 --> 22:57.836
I know. Can't seem to stop it.

22:57.919 --> 22:59.713
(Rebecca chuckles)

23:01.756 --> 23:02.841
(sniffs)

23:06.720 --> 23:08.930
(faucet running)

23:10.140 --> 23:12.142
(phone ringing)

23:19.232 --> 23:21.317
Jae-won, it's late, buddy.

23:22.736 --> 23:24.362
Push the meeting.

23:25.947 --> 23:28.116
I don't know, man. There's a lot
going on right now.

23:28.199 --> 23:29.701
Just, um...

23:29.784 --> 23:33.288
need to find some more runway
to kick this can, okay?

23:34.456 --> 23:36.624
(sucks teeth)
All right, later.

23:40.545 --> 23:42.839
What can is being kicked?

23:44.049 --> 23:45.342
Um...

23:46.343 --> 23:49.387
Senior Senator from Pennsylvania
keeps calling,

23:49.471 --> 23:50.805
wanting to meet.

23:52.807 --> 23:54.100
Why don't you want
to meet with him?

23:54.184 --> 23:55.268
It sounds important.

23:55.352 --> 23:56.811
Uh, it's complicated.

23:56.895 --> 23:59.189
Well, okay.

23:59.272 --> 24:02.776
Well, if you don't want
to talk about it, I won't pry.

24:04.778 --> 24:06.571
(exhales noisily)

24:18.124 --> 24:21.169
You know that article,
the five fun facts?

24:21.252 --> 24:23.046
Mm-hmm.

24:25.048 --> 24:26.800
It's not just a fluff piece.

24:26.883 --> 24:29.135
It's part of a bigger strategy.

24:31.262 --> 24:33.556
I've been getting these calls
from the DNC,

24:33.640 --> 24:36.476
this, um, Senator Gamble,
in particular.

24:37.477 --> 24:39.104
He's retiring next year,

24:39.187 --> 24:40.980
and he's put my name
on a short list

24:41.064 --> 24:42.774
of potential people
to replace him.

24:42.857 --> 24:45.610
-Now, it's a long shot, Mom.
-What?

24:45.694 --> 24:47.445
I don't have a national profile,

24:47.529 --> 24:51.324
but, uh, the first election
got a lot of attention, and, uh,

24:51.408 --> 24:53.618
this rehab initiative
is getting some more, so...

24:53.702 --> 24:56.496
Oh, my God, Randall.

24:56.579 --> 24:58.832
-Ma.
-You are gonna be a senator?

24:58.915 --> 25:01.584
-No, I'm not, Ma. (laughs)
-(chuckles)

25:01.668 --> 25:05.463
I haven't even decided if it's
something I'm interested yet.

25:05.547 --> 25:07.716
All right? Beth just got settled
into her dance academy.

25:07.799 --> 25:10.677
I can't put her through
another campaign.

25:13.722 --> 25:15.807
I just don't want to make
any major life decisions

25:15.890 --> 25:19.811
with so much uncertainty
in the family.

25:19.894 --> 25:21.438
You know?

25:21.521 --> 25:22.939
Mm.

25:25.275 --> 25:27.277
Yeah, I understand.

25:27.360 --> 25:28.570
(inhales)

25:28.653 --> 25:30.655
♪ ♪

25:38.872 --> 25:40.874
♪ ♪

25:47.172 --> 25:48.715
(children giggling)

25:52.510 --> 25:54.179
And that is how you get it done.

25:54.262 --> 25:55.430
Killer job, Randall.

25:55.513 --> 25:57.724
It is my great honor
to now certify

25:57.807 --> 26:00.268
that you are allowed
in the deep end, kiddo,

26:00.352 --> 26:01.728
with the big kids.

26:01.811 --> 26:03.313
No more limits.

26:03.396 --> 26:04.689
Let me let the lifeguards know.

26:04.773 --> 26:06.024
Congratulations.

26:07.233 --> 26:09.903
-REBECCA: How'd she do?
-(Jack scoffs)

26:09.986 --> 26:11.446
Today is not the day.

26:13.907 --> 26:15.909
♪ ♪

26:30.173 --> 26:32.634
(breathes deeply)

26:33.885 --> 26:36.262
(footsteps approaching)

26:37.305 --> 26:38.473
Settled the bill.

26:38.556 --> 26:39.891
Ready to go?

26:41.101 --> 26:42.268
Yeah.

26:43.478 --> 26:45.480
Will you sit with me
for a minute?

26:45.563 --> 26:47.565
(clicks tongue)
Okay, but just for minute.

26:47.649 --> 26:49.859
If we hit the road by 11:00,

26:49.943 --> 26:53.238
-we'll be in Boston in time
to get back to Philly... Okay.
-Just sit. Please.

26:53.321 --> 26:54.864
(Randall groans)

26:54.948 --> 26:56.533
(Rebecca sighs)

27:03.331 --> 27:04.666
(chuckles)

27:05.667 --> 27:08.128
I remember watching you swim
as a little boy.

27:08.211 --> 27:11.339
You took to it so fast.

27:12.340 --> 27:14.718
That first summer,
you were just all...

27:14.801 --> 27:17.846
<i>(chuckles)</i>
<i>...skinny limbs and...</i>

27:17.929 --> 27:21.057
flailing arms,
but you were still so good.

27:21.141 --> 27:23.268
-(clicks tongue)
-Yeah.

27:23.351 --> 27:26.312
And then the next summer,
you were a little bigger.

27:28.148 --> 27:29.816
And then the summer after that.

27:29.899 --> 27:31.776
You kids just kept changing.

27:33.028 --> 27:35.405
Getting better and better,
and stronger and stronger.

27:35.488 --> 27:36.573
Every...

27:37.866 --> 27:40.118
...second, every day,

27:40.201 --> 27:42.203
every year, you just...

27:43.830 --> 27:45.206
...you became.

27:48.626 --> 27:50.628
It was quite a thing for me...

27:51.880 --> 27:56.092
...having a front-row seat
to the best show in town.

28:02.515 --> 28:04.893
I know you're worried about me,
sweetheart.

28:04.976 --> 28:06.353
-Oh, Mom, I'm not even...
-No, no.

28:06.436 --> 28:07.687
It's okay.

28:08.688 --> 28:10.607
This...

28:10.690 --> 28:13.943
this disease has taken
its toll on everybody...

28:14.027 --> 28:15.278
(inhales)

28:15.362 --> 28:17.364
...but on you, especially.

28:21.076 --> 28:22.369
(inhales)

28:23.870 --> 28:27.123
When your dad died,
you just, uh...

28:27.207 --> 28:29.167
you really rose
to the occasion, Randall.

28:29.250 --> 28:31.920
Any time I needed you,
you were there.

28:32.962 --> 28:36.424
I used to think you kind of
became my rock after Dad,

28:36.508 --> 28:38.426
but in reality,

28:38.510 --> 28:41.721
no, this thing you and I have,

28:41.805 --> 28:44.015
that was there long before then.

28:45.892 --> 28:48.728
I mean,
Dad didn't love to read,

28:48.812 --> 28:51.439
-so you read with me.
-(chuckles)

28:51.523 --> 28:54.317
And then, when your dad died,

28:54.401 --> 28:56.277
you didn't end up going to
the college that you wanted to

28:56.361 --> 28:58.446
-so you could be near me.
-That's not true.

28:58.530 --> 29:00.573
It is true. It's very true.

29:00.657 --> 29:02.200
You-you took care of me.

29:03.201 --> 29:05.245
Which, yes,

29:05.328 --> 29:09.124
it is the natural course
for parents and children.

29:09.207 --> 29:12.419
Eventually, but not that soon.

29:13.503 --> 29:15.213
Not that early.

29:16.381 --> 29:17.799
It was...

29:17.882 --> 29:20.051
it was a lot to ask of you.

29:20.135 --> 29:22.053
It was, it was too much.

29:27.809 --> 29:30.520
And that is why I couldn't
make you the executor.

29:32.230 --> 29:35.358
Because you and I both know
you would move heaven and earth

29:35.442 --> 29:36.735
to see me get better,

29:36.818 --> 29:40.321
and you would stop
your entire life for me.

29:40.405 --> 29:42.782
-And I can't let you do that.
-(sniffles)

29:42.866 --> 29:44.200
Not anymore.

29:52.292 --> 29:54.669
You are my hero, Randall.

29:56.379 --> 29:58.673
You're the most
incredible person,

29:58.757 --> 30:00.592
and I...

30:00.675 --> 30:04.012
I will not be the person
that holds you back anymore.

30:04.095 --> 30:05.638
-You've never been that.
-No, I know.

30:05.722 --> 30:07.515
-I know.
-(exhales)

30:07.599 --> 30:08.933
I know.

30:11.978 --> 30:13.980
♪ ♪

30:16.775 --> 30:18.026
(sniffles)

30:18.109 --> 30:19.444
(exhales)

30:19.527 --> 30:20.779
(sniffles)

30:20.862 --> 30:22.155
(clears throat)

30:25.075 --> 30:27.911
Hey, can I say something
that sounds obnoxious

30:27.994 --> 30:29.829
that I can only say to you?

30:31.039 --> 30:34.042
-Well, yes,
that's what I'm here for.
-(chuckles)

30:38.421 --> 30:41.841
If I do this thing,
I'll win, Mom.

30:45.762 --> 30:47.806
If I run, I'll win.

30:49.015 --> 30:50.475
And if I win,

30:50.558 --> 30:53.395
I can't even imagine
where this thing will end.

30:54.396 --> 30:55.855
I can.

30:55.939 --> 30:58.441
I can see it very clearly.

31:01.986 --> 31:03.738
-(phone ringing)
-(sniffles)

31:03.822 --> 31:05.365
(sighs)

31:06.825 --> 31:08.243
It's Deja.

31:10.078 --> 31:11.329
Hello.

31:13.164 --> 31:14.457
Hey, Dej.

31:17.002 --> 31:18.545
I'm on my way right now.

31:25.010 --> 31:26.970
(engine shuts off)

31:28.471 --> 31:29.764
-(seat belt unbuckling)
-REBECCA: Hey.

31:29.848 --> 31:31.224
Gentle.

31:31.307 --> 31:34.269
(breathes deeply)

31:46.823 --> 31:48.533
(sniffling)

32:09.763 --> 32:11.890
You know, I didn't do this
because of you.

32:16.686 --> 32:18.938
No, um... (exhales)

32:19.022 --> 32:20.648
...it just wasn't fair to her.

32:22.442 --> 32:23.985
For either of us, really.

32:31.326 --> 32:33.370
I just love her so much.

32:38.249 --> 32:41.002
That's the thing
about first loves, man.

32:42.462 --> 32:44.547
They form you

32:44.631 --> 32:47.634
and can stay with you
for the rest of your life.

32:49.511 --> 32:50.679
Yeah.

32:55.684 --> 32:57.811
You know, these things have
a way of coming back around,

32:57.894 --> 32:59.938
Malik, if they're meant to be.

33:00.021 --> 33:03.775
A person can walk out the door
and that's the end,

33:03.858 --> 33:07.821
but sometimes, the door reopens.

33:12.742 --> 33:14.119
Thank you...

33:15.286 --> 33:17.455
...for looking out for me,

33:17.539 --> 33:18.707
being my mentor.

33:18.790 --> 33:20.208
It really meant a lot.

33:23.753 --> 33:25.338
You're a good kid, Malik.

33:25.422 --> 33:27.632
You're a very good kid.

33:29.426 --> 33:31.344
You take care of yourself, okay?

33:50.196 --> 33:52.115
(sighing)

34:07.255 --> 34:11.176
Everything has been
so intense for us,

34:11.259 --> 34:13.678
since we got together.

34:15.930 --> 34:17.390
And I guess...

34:19.684 --> 34:21.644
...maybe in-in the future...

34:23.396 --> 34:25.148
...just not now.

34:34.824 --> 34:36.993
I'm sorry about what I said.

34:39.829 --> 34:42.957
I don't want to have a whole
talk about it right now...

34:45.627 --> 34:47.420
...but you're my dad.

34:50.090 --> 34:52.092
You're the only one I ever had.

35:04.562 --> 35:06.564
♪ ♪

35:16.116 --> 35:17.909
Let's go home.

35:26.001 --> 35:26.918
Mm.

35:27.002 --> 35:28.878
Hey. Mom all good?

35:28.962 --> 35:30.839
Yeah.

35:31.881 --> 35:34.092
Okay, I got to ask, man.

35:34.175 --> 35:35.719
What did you tell the cop?

35:35.802 --> 35:37.971
Seriously. What'd you say?

35:40.348 --> 35:41.891
-Excuse me, sir?
-Whoa.

35:41.975 --> 35:43.685
Just 30 seconds.

35:48.023 --> 35:50.442
My father died two years ago.

35:52.068 --> 35:54.738
And my-my siblings over there,
they're...

35:57.699 --> 35:59.909
Actually, we're struggling.

36:00.952 --> 36:03.079
Sir, I've been trying to carry
this family on my back

36:03.163 --> 36:05.165
for the past two years, and...

36:05.248 --> 36:07.625
I don't know
if I'm doing it well.

36:08.668 --> 36:10.587
But if we break tonight,

36:10.670 --> 36:12.464
if my mom has to get a call

36:12.547 --> 36:14.549
that her three children
are in trouble...

36:15.800 --> 36:18.136
...there's a very real chance
we won't make it.

36:22.474 --> 36:24.809
Oh, and I may end up
being president one day.

36:24.893 --> 36:26.227
So...

36:26.311 --> 36:28.188
I really can't get arrested.

36:30.774 --> 36:31.691
<i>Like I said,</i>

36:31.775 --> 36:33.234
he was a reasonable guy.

36:33.318 --> 36:35.362
I just asked him
to look at you two,

36:35.445 --> 36:36.988
to really look at you,

36:37.072 --> 36:38.114
and tell me if he thought

36:38.198 --> 36:39.866
you guys would last one night
in jail.

36:39.949 --> 36:41.743
-He did not.
-(laughing)

36:41.826 --> 36:43.578
(laughing):
Shut up!

36:43.661 --> 36:45.663
♪ ♪

36:53.463 --> 36:55.799
(inhaling deeply)

36:55.882 --> 36:57.884
(exhales)

37:09.437 --> 37:11.648
♪ ♪

37:14.109 --> 37:15.860
(chuckles softly)

37:17.070 --> 37:19.239
What a strange thing.

37:19.322 --> 37:21.408
What?

37:24.327 --> 37:26.329
All of it.

37:48.101 --> 37:50.103
♪ ♪

37:56.234 --> 37:57.360
<i>RANDALL:</i>
<i>Miguel, thanks</i>

37:57.444 --> 37:58.361
for sticking around, man.

37:58.445 --> 38:00.363
Oh, anytime, Randall. Of course.

38:00.447 --> 38:01.865
You guys have a safe trip back.

38:01.948 --> 38:03.950
-And call us when you get there,
okay?
-We will.

38:04.034 --> 38:06.036
-Good to see you. Mmm.
-You, too. Thank you.
-Take care.

38:06.119 --> 38:08.038
-You got it? You got it?
-Thanks for everything.
-Of course.

38:08.121 --> 38:10.415
-Migs. Mwah.
-Mmm.
-That was so much fun.

38:10.498 --> 38:11.541
-It was a blast.
-MIGUEL and BETH: See you soon.

38:11.624 --> 38:13.126
-Thanks, Mom.
-Mm.

38:14.627 --> 38:16.880
Could I get one more selfie
for the road?

38:16.963 --> 38:19.090
-I'll wait in the car.
-(laughs)

38:19.174 --> 38:20.550
Why not?

38:20.633 --> 38:21.718
Come on.

38:21.801 --> 38:23.011
(chuckles)

38:23.094 --> 38:24.429
Here we go.

38:24.512 --> 38:25.513
Mmm.

38:25.597 --> 38:27.265
-Cheese.
-(chuckles softly)

38:29.059 --> 38:29.976
Oh.

38:30.060 --> 38:32.395
-That reminds me.
-What?

38:32.479 --> 38:35.023
Could you sign this for me,
please?

38:36.066 --> 38:37.817
It's gonna be worth
a lot of money one day, and...

38:37.901 --> 38:39.819
-I should leave something
for Miguel.
-(chuckles)

38:39.903 --> 38:42.781
Well, in that case...

38:44.866 --> 38:47.285
Ah.
(chuckles softly)

38:48.787 --> 38:50.789
("Where Do the Children Play?"
by Cat Stevens playing)

38:53.249 --> 38:55.251
(indistinct chatter)

38:59.381 --> 39:01.299
Hey, bud!

39:01.383 --> 39:02.509
How'd it go?
Did you pass the test?

39:02.592 --> 39:04.594
-Yeah, I did.
-You did?

39:04.678 --> 39:07.097
-Good job, bud.
-Good job.

39:07.180 --> 39:08.973
You guys want
to come in with me?

39:09.057 --> 39:12.644
You know what, I think
we're all a little tired.

39:12.727 --> 39:14.145
So maybe next time.

39:18.608 --> 39:20.026
-Tag! You're it!
-No way!

39:20.110 --> 39:21.111
-All right.
-(splashing)

39:23.029 --> 39:24.030
(chuckles softly)

39:25.532 --> 39:26.783
JACK:
Hey, boys!

39:26.866 --> 39:28.326
-Boys.
-(chuckles)

39:28.410 --> 39:30.578
-(laughing)
-Hold on a second.

39:30.662 --> 39:32.247
-Hold on a second.
-KEVIN: Kate!

39:32.330 --> 39:34.833
-KEVIN and RANDALL: Come on!
Come on!
-Oh, Kate! Come on, Kate!

39:34.916 --> 39:36.418
-KEVIN: Come on!
-♪ <i>Well, I think it's fine</i> ♪

39:36.501 --> 39:38.586
JACK:
Come on, Kate. Okay, okay.

39:38.670 --> 39:40.964
-♪ <i>Building jumbo planes</i> ♪
-I got you.

39:42.841 --> 39:45.093
♪ <i>Or taking a ride</i> ♪

39:45.176 --> 39:46.511
-Oh.
-(laughing)

39:46.594 --> 39:48.972
-♪ <i>On a cosmic train</i> ♪
-Here it is.

39:50.390 --> 39:52.308
-♪ <i>Switch on summer</i> ♪
-(children shouting)

39:52.392 --> 39:54.185
-Come in!
-Come on, Mom!

39:54.269 --> 39:55.687
♪ <i>From a slot machine</i> ♪

39:55.770 --> 39:57.605
-(chuckles): Okay!
-So fun!
-Mom!

39:58.857 --> 40:01.526
♪ <i>I know we've come a long way</i> ♪

40:01.609 --> 40:05.321
♪ <i>We're changing day to day</i> ♪

40:05.405 --> 40:07.282
♪ <i>But tell me</i> ♪

40:07.365 --> 40:13.288
♪ <i>Where do the children play?</i> ♪

40:23.590 --> 40:25.508
♪ <i>Well, you roll on roads</i> ♪

40:26.843 --> 40:30.055
♪ <i>Over fresh green grass</i> ♪

40:31.139 --> 40:33.475
♪ <i>For your lorry loads</i> ♪

40:34.893 --> 40:37.062
♪ <i>Pumping petrol gas</i> ♪

40:38.855 --> 40:40.774
Hey, Jae-won.

40:40.857 --> 40:42.317
No more kicking the can.

40:42.400 --> 40:44.444
Let's lock in Monday morning
for that meeting

40:44.527 --> 40:46.404
with Senator Gamble.

40:46.488 --> 40:49.199
♪ <i>But they just go on and on</i> ♪

40:49.282 --> 40:52.243
♪ <i>And it seems</i>
<i>that you can't get off</i> ♪

40:53.912 --> 40:55.497
♪ <i>Oh</i> ♪

40:55.580 --> 40:58.667
♪ <i>I know we've come a long way</i> ♪

40:58.750 --> 41:00.835
♪ <i>We're changing day to day</i> ♪

41:00.919 --> 41:02.504
Hi!

41:02.587 --> 41:04.714
(quietly):
They're both sleeping.

41:04.798 --> 41:06.716
The prodigal twins
have returned.

41:06.800 --> 41:08.510
You're impressed. Admit it.

41:08.593 --> 41:10.178
I am.

41:10.261 --> 41:13.056
♪ ♪

41:18.353 --> 41:21.439
(pants)
Did you, uh...

41:21.523 --> 41:24.067
fill Sheila's job yet?

41:24.150 --> 41:26.820
<i>PHILLIP:</i>
<i>Uh, no. But we're looking</i>
<i>at applicants.</i>

41:26.903 --> 41:29.280
I'd like to be considered.

41:29.364 --> 41:33.618
♪ <i>Oh, oh</i> ♪

41:33.702 --> 41:36.121
♪ <i>Well, you've cracked the sky</i> ♪

41:36.204 --> 41:37.122
(exhales)

41:37.205 --> 41:39.499
♪ <i>Scrapers fill the air</i> ♪

41:40.500 --> 41:43.169
♪ <i>But will you keep on</i>
<i>building higher</i> ♪

41:43.253 --> 41:44.337
Hey.

41:44.421 --> 41:46.840
I've got, uh, some good news.

41:46.923 --> 41:48.675
The, um...

41:48.758 --> 41:50.135
smoker arrived in time

41:50.218 --> 41:52.470
for your mom and Miguel's
anniversary party.

41:52.554 --> 41:55.098
♪ <i>Will you make us cry?</i> ♪

41:56.099 --> 41:58.852
I am not ready
to move to San Francisco.

41:58.935 --> 42:00.937
Not with where we are right now.

42:01.938 --> 42:03.398
I'm sorry.

42:04.399 --> 42:07.152
♪ <i>I know we've come a long way</i> ♪

42:07.235 --> 42:10.572
♪ <i>We're changing day to day</i> ♪

42:10.655 --> 42:12.365
♪ <i>But tell me</i> ♪

42:12.449 --> 42:18.455
♪ <i>Where do the children play?</i> ♪

42:21.207 --> 42:24.085
♪ <i>Oh, do-do-do</i> ♪

42:24.169 --> 42:25.795
♪ <i>Do-do-do-do-do.</i> ♪

